<br>
There are many reason for me leaving AxS and my friends behind, but I'll give you the biggest and most important.  My time playing will be limited again very soon, I work in the IT industry and for the government, and at this point in the worlds state of affairs, I will be very involved in RL for an unseen amount of time.  My broken ankle is just a temporary escape from my workload, and that will be returning to normal in the upcoming weeks (hopefully)<br>
<br>
I still have regular time slots(1-2 times a week max) for EQ, but I want to start spending these with my RL friends and family that also play the game.  I've never really been big on raids and the highend game, and I lack an understanding of many of the concepts which has made me seem a &quot;Nuub&quot; as Fargus accurately puts it =).  My main goal in game is mostly just screwing off, and I've felt a little confined in the guild from time to time.  I love that the guild has taken on a new level of structure and organization, but that is all my RL is, and I play EQ to get away from that.<br>
<br>
My hope is that there isn't any hard feelings with my leaving, and I want you to know I'm here to help any of you with anything, at anytime, anywhere.  Beker will soon have a tailoring skill of 250 (my personal goal by May 1st.) so if you need a master tailor for anything this summer let me know.<br>
<br>
Fargus, you have a great guild here full of very good individuals.  I admire your commitment to all of them (as many of them are very good friends of mine)  and I really do hope that your new ideas and actions help all of the members attain their personal ingame goals.<br>
<br>
I hope all of you get to see the endgame content before EQ1 snaps out (if it ever will) and I wish all of you the very best in both RL and ingame.  I had planned on quitting EQ after leaving AxS because this guild is the main reason I played.  My family and RL friends that play convinced me otherwise, and I even had a few people reopen their accounts to rekindle some of the lost fun that we all once had a couple years ago..... <br>
<br>
I digress<br>
<br>
